{"questionId":"19884371","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The owner of a convenience store installs two security cameras, represented by points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C1</mtext></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C2</mtext></math>. Both cameras point towards the centre of the store’s cash register, represented by&nbsp;the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>R</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p>The following diagram shows this information on a cross-section of the store.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/9388cbda1721d4d6b12a81270e2ecc8334ddc319.png\"></p>\n<p>The cameras are positioned at a height of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>, and the horizontal distance between the&nbsp;cameras is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>. The cash register is sitting on a counter so that its centre, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>R</mtext></math>, is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math> above the floor.</p>\n<p>The distance from Camera <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> to the centre of the cash register is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Determine the angle of depression from Camera <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> to the centre of the cash register. Give your answer in degrees.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>85202</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mn>48</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>48</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5903</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19884371","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ2.3a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Determine the angle of depression from Camera 1 to the centre of the cash register. Give your answer in degrees.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Angles of elevation and depression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}